did.abstract: The materials consist of videotaped interviews with members of the Yale College Class of 1958 and a speech by Donald M. Caruthers given at their 50th Class reunion.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 10-A (YRG 10-A), Records of Yale College classes.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Class of 1958, Yale College, Records (RU 353). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of videotaped interviews with members of the Yale College Class of 1958. Also includes a speech delivered by Donald Crothers at the 50th class reunion.

did.unittitle: "58 Men" feature documentary on the Yale Class of 1958 [Video recordings]

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials in this collection were created as part of the feature length documentary, "58 Men" produced in 1993 for the Yale Class of 1958's 35th reunion. The roughly 350 interviews with classmates were conducted by filmmakers Steve Bergman, MMPM '92 and John Boulet, MMPM '92 across the United States and Paris, France. The documentary is narrated by Dick Cavett '58, written by C.D.B. Bryan '58, and produced by Joel Schiavone '58 and Jack Embersits '58.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: These materials were donated by Steven Bergman, MBA'92 in 1993.
